<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFBFFDAA5CDFE3B1A0CFD38" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFBFFDAA5CDFE3B1CA9FE3D" blockId="11.[136,662,482,509]" box="[136,662,482,509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFFBFFDAA5CDFE3B1CA9FE3D" box="[136,662,482,509]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" reason="4">
5. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA5E1FE3B1C3BFE3D" authority="J. F. Gmelin (1791" authorityName="J. F. Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[164,516,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA5E1FE3B1F0DFE3D" bold="true" box="[164,306,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Glandularia</emphasis>
J.F. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA41FFE3B1C3BFE3D" author="Gmelin, J. F." box="[346,516,482,509]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="886 - 920" refId="ref34695" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1791 [1792]) Glandularia. Systema Naturae [...] editio decima tertia, aucta, reformata 2: 886 - 920." type="journal article" year="1791">Gmelin (1791</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[1792]: 886).
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFBFFDAA5CDFDF31A0CFD38" blockId="11.[136,1452,554,1049]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Herbs, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences terminal, compound, racemes spiciform, multiflorous; rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, green; bracteoles absent. Flowers sessile; calyx tubular, shorter than the corolla, membranaceous, green, 5-lobed, accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 4, included, didynamous, superior pair with or without connective appendages, thecae parallel; ovary 2-carpelate, 4-loculate, ovules 1 per locule, style three times longer than the ovary, stigma 2-lobed. Fruit a schizocarp, with 4 cluses, brown, external surface reticulate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFFBFFDAA5F8FCDB1A0EFBD8" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFFBFFDAA5F8FCDB1A0EFBD8" blockId="11.[136,1452,554,1049]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA5F8FCDB1F78FCDC" authorityName="J. F. Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[189,327,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA5F8FCDB1F78FCDC" box="[189,327,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Glandularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA773FCDB1DAEFCDC" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[566,913,770,796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Verbeneae">
Verbeneae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA7FBFCDB1DB6FCDC" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[702,905,770,796]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA642FCDA1D7BFCDC" box="[775,836,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and presents 88 species disjunctly distributed throughout the subtropical and temperate regions of the North and South America (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA17CFCFF1B05FC80" author="Peralta, P. &amp; Thode, V." box="[1081,1338,806,832]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="32" refId="ref37323" refString="Peralta, P. &amp; Thode, V. (2010) Una nueva especie, un nuevo status y nuevas combinaciones en Glandularia (Verbenaceae) para el Sur de Brazil. Rodriguesia 61: S 29 - S 32. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201061128" type="journal article" year="2010">Peralta &amp; Thode 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA003FCFF1F7DFCA4" author="Thode, V. &amp; Bordignon, S. A. L." pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref39574" refString="Thode, V. &amp; Bordignon, S. A. L. (2019) Two new species of Glandularia (Verbenaceae) from Rio Grande do Sul and an updated key to the species occurring in Brazil. Phytotaxa 441: 39 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 411.1.3" type="journal article" year="2019">Thode &amp; Bordignon 2019</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA4F4FC921FD5FCA4" box="[433,490,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2020c, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA7E2FC921D7AFCA4" box="[679,837,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). The genus is characterized by the style three or more times longer than the ovary, stem with cortical chlorenchyma in a continuous band, and chromosomic number equal to five and multiples (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA4C2FC4B1C9BFC6C" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Peralta, P." box="[391,676,914,940]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="218 - 230" refId="ref36683" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Peralta, P. (2007) Nuevas combinaciones en el genero Glandularia (Verbenaceace). Darwiniana 47: 218 - 230." type="journal article" year="2007">O’Leary &amp; Peralta 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The main diversity centers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFFBFFDAA157FC4B1AA3FC6C" authorityName="J. F. Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[1042,1180,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Glandularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA157FC4B1AA3FC6C" box="[1042,1180,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Glandularia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the south region of 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFFBFFDAA5CDFC6F1EF3FC10" box="[136,204,950,976]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFFBFFDAA4D1FC6F1C3CFC10" box="[404,515,950,976]" name="Argentina" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA757FC6F1D1CFC11" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V." box="[530,803,950,977]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="699 - 750" refId="ref36712" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V. (2016) The genus Glandularia (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 101: 699 - 750. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2014008" type="journal article" year="2016">O’Leary &amp; Thode 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFFBFFDAA611FC6F1DA4FC10" box="[852,923,950,976]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, there are 34 species recorded, of which 13 are endemic and 26 are found in the Atlantic Forest domain (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA642FC031A2BFC34" author="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V." box="[775,1044,986,1012]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="699 - 750" refId="ref36712" refString="O'Leary, N. &amp; Thode, V. (2016) The genus Glandularia (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 101: 699 - 750. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2014008" type="journal article" year="2016">O’Leary &amp; Thode 2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFFBFFDAA15BFC031B7CFC34" author="Thode, V. &amp; Bordignon, S. A. L." box="[1054,1347,986,1012]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref39574" refString="Thode, V. &amp; Bordignon, S. A. L. (2019) Two new species of Glandularia (Verbenaceae) from Rio Grande do Sul and an updated key to the species occurring in Brazil. Phytotaxa 441: 39 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 411.1.3" type="journal article" year="2019">Thode &amp; Bordignon 2019</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA5CDFC261EFFFBD8" box="[136,192,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2020c, O’Leary 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFFBFFDAA43AFC261F87FBD8" box="[383,440,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">et al.</emphasis>
2020). One species occurs in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFFBFFDAA6CFFC271A12FBD8" box="[906,1069,1022,1048]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
